WTI crude futures strengthened above $76 per barrel on Monday  extending gains from the previous session as investors look ahead to an OPEC+ meeting over the weekend  where the group is expected to deepen supply cuts to support oil prices.On Friday  crude prices jumped about 4%after OPEC+ told Reuters it is considering whether to make additional supply cuts when it meets on Nov. 26. Analysts also expect Saudi Arabia and Russia to roll over additional voluntary cuts into early next year. Still  oil prices remained down about 20% from September highs amid signs of robust supplies and as the war-risk premium generated by the Israel-Hamas conflict faded away. Latest data pointed to surging crude oil inventories in the US  while Russia recently lifted a ban on gasoline exports.
